<article class="post-body">

    <!-- INTRODUCTION -->
    <p>Compressing a PDF file is one of the most common tasks for students and job seekers preparing government application forms. Most online portals have a strict file size limit — often under 100KB or 200KB — and submitting an oversized file leads to instant rejection.</p>

    <p>In this guide, you will learn exactly <strong>how to compress a PDF online for free</strong> without losing text clarity or image quality, using Rojgar Sangam Tools.</p>

    <!-- TIP BOX EXAMPLE -->
    <div class="tip-box">
        <div class="tip-title"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> Quick Tip</div>
        <p>Most government portals like SSC, UPSC, and Railway accept PDF files between 100KB and 500KB. Always check the exact limit before uploading.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- H2 SECTION -->
    <h2>Why Does PDF File Size Matter for Govt Forms?</h2>
    <p>When you fill an online government job application, you are required to upload several documents — marksheets, certificates, photo, signature, and more. Each document has a maximum size limit defined by the portal.</p>
    <p>If your PDF exceeds the limit, the form will not accept the upload. This is why compressing your PDF before submission is essential.</p>

    <!-- WARNING BOX EXAMPLE -->
    <div class="warning-box">
        <div class="tip-title"><i class="fas fa-triangle-exclamation"></i> Important Warning</div>
        <p>Do not compress a PDF more than required. Over-compression makes text blurry and unreadable, which may cause your application to be rejected during document verification.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- H2 WITH STEP LIST -->
    <h2>How to Compress PDF Online Free — Step by Step</h2>
    <p>Follow these simple steps to reduce your PDF file size instantly using our free tool:</p>

    <ol class="step-list">
        <li>
            <div class="step-num">1</div>
            <div class="step-text">
                <strong>Open the Compress PDF Tool</strong>
                <p>Go to <a href="/tools/compress-pdf">Rojgar Sangam Tools — Compress PDF</a>. No signup or installation is required.</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        <li>
            <div class="step-num">2</div>
            <div class="step-text">
                <strong>Upload Your PDF File</strong>
                <p>Click the upload button or drag and drop your PDF file directly onto the page. Files are processed in your browser only — never uploaded to any server.</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        <li>
            <div class="step-num">3</div>
            <div class="step-text">
                <strong>Select Compression Level</strong>
                <p>Choose between Low, Medium, or High compression depending on your target file size and quality requirement.</p>
            </div>
        </li>
        <li>
            <div class="step-num">4</div>
            <div class="step-text">
                <strong>Download Your Compressed PDF</strong>
                <p>Click the Compress button and download your optimised PDF instantly. Check the file size before uploading to the form portal.</p>
            </div>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <!-- H2 SECTION -->
    <h2>Recommended Compression Settings by Portal</h2>

    <h3>For SSC and UPSC Applications</h3>
    <p>Most SSC and UPSC portals require documents under <strong>200KB</strong>. Use Medium compression for scanned certificates and Low compression for digital PDFs.</p>

    <h3>For Railway and State Government Portals</h3>
    <p>Railway portals typically accept up to <strong>500KB</strong>. Low compression is usually sufficient here, which preserves better quality.</p>

    <h3>For Bank and IBPS Applications</h3>
    <p>Bank portals usually allow up to <strong>300KB</strong>. Medium compression works best for most document types.</p>

    <!-- CTA BOX -->
    <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Compress Your PDF Right Now — Free</h3>
        <p>No signup required. Works on all devices. 100% browser-based and secure.</p>
        <a href="/tools/compress-pdf" class="cta-btn">
            <i class="fas fa-compress"></i> Open Compress PDF Tool
        </a>
    </div>

    <!-- H2 SECTION -->
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>Is my PDF file safe when I compress it?</h3>
    <p>Yes, completely. All compression happens directly in your browser. Your file is never sent to any server. Once you close the tab, the file is gone.</p>

    <h3>Can I compress a PDF on mobile?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Rojgar Sangam Tools works on all devices — desktop, tablet, and mobile — without any app installation.</p>

    <h3>Will compressing reduce text quality?</h3>
    <p>Low and Medium compression settings preserve text sharpness completely. Only High compression may slightly reduce image quality inside the PDF.</p>

</article>
